health stamp
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an annual postage stamp which includes a levy for support of health camps; a postage stamp, formerly issued annually, part of extra value of which went towards supporting health camps.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: The health stamps were first produced in 1929, following an appeal in 1928 by Danish immigrant Kirstine Nielsen.
